# Muni, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Muni (; ) is a [https://www.freetechmasala.com/ rural locality] (a selo) and the administrative centre of Muninsky Selsoviet, Botlikhsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 3,220 as of 2010. There are 45 streets.
Geography
Muni is located 10&nbsp;km northeast of Botlikh (the district's administrative centre) by road, on the Unsatlen River. Kvankhidatli is the nearest rural locality.
